news.title: New Noida, with 60 Bulandshahr villages in it, on fast track as 'investment region'
news.para: Also known as 'New Noida', the region will be developed across 20,000 hectares comprising 80 villages - 20 in Gautam Budh Nagar and 60 in Bulandshahr.

news.title: Only 17% of targeted dwelling units completed in Karnataka for urban poor: CAG
news.para: ​It also said that out of Affordable Housing in Partnership (AHP) and Beneficiary Led Individual House Construction (BLC) projects were taken up for only 5,17,531 beneficiaries out of the 13,71,592 prospective beneficiaries (38 per cent) identified through demand survey as on March 2021.

news.title: Karnataka: Bill to regularise gram panchayat properties passed
news.para: During the proceedings, a debate en sued over whether regularisation of these properties would facilitate illegal layouts developed by small-time developers and the land mafia.

news.title: Housing schemes riddled with irregularities in Karnataka: CAG
news.para: As per the report, of the beneficiaries listed in the detailed project reports (DPR) prepared for the affordable housing projects, 1,600 of the 12,979 beneficiaries were given the housing.

news.title: Karnataka HC restrains PNB Housing from taking coercive measures against homebuyers
news.para: The Karnataka High Court issued a writ of Mandamus on September 14 restraining the PNB Housing Finance Limited from taking any coercive measures against home buyers who filed complaints for recovering any amount in the loan agreements and Tripartite agreements.

news.title: Adani Group pledges shares of ACC, Ambuja Cements worth about $12.5 billion
news.para: The pledged shares of ACC and Ambuja were worth around 989.46 billion rupees based on Monday's closing prices and accounted for a 57% stake in ACC and a 63% stake in Ambuja Cements.

news.title: Mumbai: Slum rehabilitation authority warns builders over rent dues
news.para: According to estimates, at least 50,000 families haven't got rent for several months, in some instances even years, in these 150 projects.

news.title: Gurugram: Fresh scare at Chintels Paradiso over cracks in balconies
news.para: The district town planner, who visited the society, said the balconies of some apartments in the two towers need immediate attention.

news.title: Pidilite Industries leases entire 10-storey office tower in Mumbai's Andheri
news.para: The company has entered into an agreement with property owner Beekalene Fabrics for the same and will be paying monthly rental of Rs 1.80 crore, taking its total pay out to Rs 119 crore across the total tenure of the lease including the escalation in rentals.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency petition against Ajnara India
news.para: According to the NCLT order, allottees were seeking to initiate CIRP against the developer for the default committed against the financial debt paid by the applicants in lieu of the units purchased in the project.

news.title: Entertainment City promoters in talks to sell Noida land for Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: Entertainment city is promoted by the Appughar and Unitech groups and there is vacant land that the new buyer can develop. The promoters have appointed real estate consultant CBRE as transaction advisor.

news.title: M&M Financial leases 275,000 sq ft office space near BKC, Mumbai
news.para: The Mahindra Group company is planning to consolidate operations of all its four entities in this newly-leased office. The company will be paying monthly rental of ₹2.50 crore, taking the total pay out to around ₹270 crore.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 17 years after township proposal, over 3,000 acres set to be returned to farmers
news.para: Two developers — Sun City and Wave Group — were supposed to acquire around 4,400 acres each. Although the land was notified for the township in 2005, the acquisition process began only in 2009-10.

news.title: Kaisa Group offshore creditors offer $2 billion to take over stalled projects: Sources
news.para: Kaisa Group, the second-largest U.S. dollar bond issuer among Chinese developers after China Evergrande Group, is in the process of restructuring its $12 billion offshore debt after defaulting on some bonds last year.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Over 29 lakh construction workers, families wait for registration under AB-PMJAY
news.para: In the state, a total of 29.93 lakh people, including 4.47 lakh registered construction workers, are yet to be registered under the Ayushman scheme and get cards, shows the order of state labour department issued to district officials.
